<html><head><meta http-equiv="Content-Type" content="text/html; charset=utf-8" /><meta http-equiv="Content-Style-Type" content="text/css" /><meta name="generator" content="Aspose.Words for .NET 13.4.0.0" /><title>The operation of the greater London Authority Act 2007 and the operation of the London Assembly – submission to the Communities and Local Government Committee</title></head><body><div><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Foundry Form Sans'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:center"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Submission from the London Assembly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold"> (FDC12)</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The London Assembly comprises 25 politicians who are elected to hold the Mayor of London to account and investigate issues of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">importance</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> to Londoners.  London Assembly Members are elected at the same time as the Mayor. Eleven represent the whole capital an</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d 14 are elected by constituencies.  The London Assembly carries out investigations into issues through cross-party committees, which often look at long-term issues facing London.  </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It also holds the Mayor to account through monthly Mayor’s Question Time me</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">etings. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he London Assembly welcomes the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">CLG Committee’s inquiry into fiscal devolution to cities and city regions. This follows the work undertaken by the London Finance Commission </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">(LFC) </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and the publication of its </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">final report, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">Raising the Capital</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">o</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">n</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> 1</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">5 May 2013.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">That report </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">examine</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> the potential for greater devolution of both taxation and the control of resources in London an</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> develop</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ed</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> options to improve </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the city’</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s tax and spending arrangements</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It recommended that London government should retain bu</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">siness rates and take full control over council tax and stamp duty land tax</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It also proposed that the yields from such taxes should be offset by a corresponding reduction in grant to ensure any changes be </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">fiscally neutral for the Exchequer</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The intention </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">is that with such additional powers, the city can</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> fund </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">infrastructure both to cater for the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">expansion </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">already forecast for its population and economy,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">and to promote additional economic growth. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The report</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> also called</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> for a relaxation of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> restrictions on bor</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">rowing for capital</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">investment within prudential rules</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The London Assembly is unanimous in </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">its support of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">principles and detailed recommendations put forward by the London Finance Commission</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. John Biggs, AM, represented the Assembly on the LFC and w</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">e </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">have also </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">had extensive discussions on the proposals with Professor</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Tony Travers, who chaired the Commission, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">when he </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">appeared in front of the London Assembly </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">on 5 June 2013. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Were the London Finance Commission recommendations to be implemented, it woul</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">d give the</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> London Mayor </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">enhanced powers over taxation and borrowing. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Assembly is firmly of the view that </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">this would need to be balanced by enhanced </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">local accountability</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">T</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">he</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> LFC report </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">recognises this</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">: </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">“If the Mayor assumed substantial additional taxat</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">ion responsibilities it would be necessary to review the Assembly’s powers with a view to enhancing them</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">” </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">This was reinforced by Professor Travers who told the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Assembly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> that “</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">the Assembly’s powers need to be strengthened pro rata</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">”</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">.</span><a name="_ftnref1"></a><a href="#_ftn1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Assembly would </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">seek a</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">dditional responsibilities in respect of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">both</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> taxation and borrowing</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">It has </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">set up a </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Financial Devolution Working Group </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">t</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">o </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">develop more detailed proposals</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">for</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Assembly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">powers with respect to</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">council tax, stamp duty land </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">tax, business rates</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">,</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">other ta</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">xes, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Tax Increment Financing schemes and the Mayor’s infrastructure plan. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Assembly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">would </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">certainly </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">seek the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ability to amend any new tax proposals by the Mayor </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">in the same way that it currently amend</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> the Mayor’s budget</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Assembly support</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">s</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> the application of the principles developed by the London Finance Commission to other English cities. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">However, </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">it is n</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">ot for the Greater London Authority</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> or the London Assembly to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">define </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">precise geographical and accountability arrangements that would </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">be appropriate for</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> such</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">devolution. That is an issue for the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">people and representatives of </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">each locality to decide. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-weight:bold">Conclusion</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">The Assembly</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">would </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">urge the Committee to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">give detailed consideration to </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">need for proper </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">governance and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">local </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">accountabilit</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">y </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">n </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the event of</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> fiscal devolution to English cities. In London, i</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">f the recommendations of the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">LFC</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> were implemented, the </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Mayor </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">would see a substantial increase in tax raising and </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">borrowing </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">powers. </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">Such</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> an expansion of the executive’s role and function sho</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">uld be effectively balanced by </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">strengthened accountability via</span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt"> </span><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">the London Assembly. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:right"><span style="font-family:'Minion Pro'; font-size:12pt; font-style:italic">January 2014</span></p><div style="width:auto; height:auto; float:right;"><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:'Foundry Form Sans'; font-size:12pt">1</span></p></div><p style="margin:0pt 18pt 0pt 0pt"><span style="font-family:'Foundry Form Sans'; font-size:12pt">&#xa0;</span></p></div><hr style="width:33%; height:1px; text-align:left" /><p style="margin:0pt"><a name="_ftn1"></a><a href="#_ftnref1">[1]</a><span style="font-family:'Foundry Form Sans'; font-size:10pt"> </span><a href="http://www.london.gov.uk/moderngov/ieListDocuments.aspx?CId=179&amp;MId=4845"><span style="color:#0000ff; font-family:'Foundry Form Sans'; font-size:10pt; text-decoration:underline">http://www.london.gov.uk/moderngov/ieListDocuments.aspx?CId=179&amp;MId=4845</span></a></p><p style="margin:0